{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at a module handoff boundary: manifest validation must gate module import/execution. A pure Unit test of validator logic can miss regressions where loader still imports plugin code. System was considered and rejected because behavior does not require subprocesses, real network, or OS-only primitives; in-process loader + temp plugin files is sufficient.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one invalid manifest (e.g., missing `name`) and an entry module that writes a side-effect marker when executed. Run the real loader over that directory. Assert: (1) loader reports validation rejection, (2) marker side effect did not occur, (3) `onLoad` was not called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.79,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module orchestration (dependency graph resolution + lifecycle invocation ordering). Unit-testing topological sort alone is insufficient because real failure can occur in the handoff from resolved order to hook execution. Higher levels are disqualified: no real OS/network/subprocess dependency and no AI/ML output dependency.","test_description":"Set up two test plugins in a temp directory: A depends on B. Each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared in-memory/event log. Run loader and assert observed hook order is `[B, A]`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.24,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Cycle detection result must propagate into load suppression. Unit graph tests can verify cycle detection algorithm, but real failure boundary is detector -> loader execution gating. System considered and rejected: no subprocess/network/OS-only behavior required.","test_description":"Create plugins A and B with mutual dependencies in manifests and `onLoad` hooks that record execution. Run loader and assert: (1) cycle is reported with both plugin names, (2) neither entry module/`onLoad` ran.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.27,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior depends on sequencing between module import side effects and lifecycle hook invocation inside the loader pipeline. A Unit test with mocked import can hide ordering bugs because the real handoff is import execution -> hook call. System was considered and rejected because this does not need subprocesses or external infrastructure; real in-process Node module loading is enough.","test_description":"Create a plugin whose entry module sets `globalThis.pluginInitFlag = true` at top-level and exports `onLoad` that asserts the flag is already true (or records timestamps/events). Run loader and assert no assertion failure and event order shows entry execution before `onLoad`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is fault-isolation and dependency-aware continuation across several modules (hook execution, error handling, dependency filtering, scheduler). Unit tests of try/catch logic are insufficient to catch real continuation/regression across plugin graph state. Higher levels are disqualified: no real OS/network/subprocess and no AI/ML dependence.","test_description":"Create three plugins: `X` throws in `onLoad`, `Y` has no dependency on `X`, `Z` depends on `X`. Run loader and assert: (1) `X` error is reported, (2) `Y` still loads, (3) `Z` does not load due to dependency on failed `X`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.16,"Integration":0.81,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
